  "The pdf is a smooth function with no discontinuities": "",
  "The distribution has no gaps": "",
  "A continuous probability distribution describes a random variable that can take any value within an interval (or the entire real line). Unlike discrete distributions, the probability of any single exact value is zero; probabilities are only meaningful for intervals.": "",
